=== verdicts vs declared expectations (docstring) ===
1. composite rule: loss ratio split/birth at iter 1000 ['767x', '18x', '493x'], final ['61x', '85x', '52x']
   -> the composite birth rule beats this split baseline by >=10x on every seed, mid-run and final.
   note: split runs DO end with negative weights (the optimizer drags weights through zero); splitting itself never flips a sign (tested directly).
2. attribution ablation (same placement and scale; only the newborn's initial weight differs):
   iter 1000: median loss birth 4.736e-06, birth_pos 4.698e-06, birth_zero 6.637e-07  (pos/signed 1.0x, zero/signed 0.1x)
   final: median loss birth 9.998e-07, birth_pos 1.258e-06, birth_zero 1.482e-07  (pos/signed 1.3x, zero/signed 0.1x)
   -> PLACEMENT dominates: newborns recover from a wrong or zero initial sign quickly (a newborn's weight sits at zero scale, so the optimizer flips it cheaply -- unlike a grown splat's). The narrative must credit the birth LOCATION, not the sign injection.
